.<img width="788" height="444" class="wp-image-1873074" style="width: 800px;" src="https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/Senator-Ademola-Adeleke.jpg" alt="" srcset="https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/Senator-Ademola-Adeleke.jpg?width=788&amp;auto_optimize=medium 788w, https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/Senator-Ademola-Adeleke-300x169.jpg?width=300&amp;auto_optimize=medium 300w, https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/Senator-Ademola-Adeleke-768x433.jpg?width=768&amp;auto_optimize=medium 768w" sizes="(max-width: 788px) 100vw, 788px" /> Governorship candidate of the People’s Democratic Party, PDP, in the June 16 Ekiti state gubernatorial election, Engineer Bisi Kolawole has congratulated the governor-elect of Osun state, Ademola Adeleke over his election victory. in a statement he personally signed, Engr. Bisi noted that the “There is no doubt that this victory will shut the doors against  misgovernance, incompetence and crass opportunism of the APC in Osun state.” He said, “I write on behalf of my self and the Peoples Democratic Party in Ekiti State to heartily rejoice with you, your deputy and the good people of Osun State on your resounding victory at the July 16 Governorship poll in Osun State. Congratulations for a new dawn in Osun.” “I salute your doggedness and courage my brother. I commend your industry and tenacity in the face of daunting odds. You have led our party to reclaim its stolen mandate in the previous 2018 Osun election. It is true that if falsehood travels for twenty years, the truth will overtake someday.” “There is no doubt that this victory will shut the doors against  misgovernance, incompetence and crass opportunism of the  All Progressive Congress in Osun State and our country Nigeria.” “You have reopened the windows of opportunities   for our people to pursue their wellbeing in an environment of peace, liberty and orderliness thereby courting for themselves the blessings of prosperity and happiness which our Party guarantees.” “Once more, Ekiti people and myself share the joy of this unique victory with you and our people in Osun as we earnestly look forward to reclaiming the government at the centre next February. It is a done deal.”    Omeiza Ajayi, Abuja As the ruling All Progressives Congress APC continues to bask in the euphoria of its landslide victory in Saturday's Governorship Election in Ekiti state, Minister of Labour and Employment, Mr Festus Keyamo SAN has urged the party not to lose focus on other upcoming elections. Keyamo in… In "Ekiti election" Former Nigerian Vice President and Peoples Democratic Party, PDP’s presidential candidate, Alhaji Atiku Abubakar and other PDP bigwigs have congratulated Osun Governor-elect, Senator Ademola Adeleke over his election victory at the just concluded Osun governorship poll. In "Osun election" Governor Ifeanyi Okowa of Delta State and Vice Presidential Candidate of the Peoples Democratic Party, PDP, Sunday, described the victory of the candidate of the party, Senator Ademola Adeleke in the Saturday's gubernatorial election as the affirmation of Osun people's will In "Osun election"